we loved watching them as we can all of us relate to at least one of these. We love watching the Best Opening Lines and Best Last Lines to discuss and see if our favourites are included. There are some very good author videos to watch and the Epic Adaptations (book-movie) videos are interesting also. If you love all things book related and want to be absolutely entertained then check out this vlog channel as it is EPIC.</p> <h2>2. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/LittleBookOwl\">Little Book Owl</a> </h2>       <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/LittleBookOwl\"                                                                        > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?wmode=opaque&list=UUYOhq5F-joK8qQPekd-jU1g\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>   <p>We like this vlogger as she has interesting videos on her channel. As well as the normal book hauls and reviews we love her bookshelf tour (who doesn’t love peeking at other people’s bookshelves?). Her book advice discussions are cool and engaging and one of the best videos is her debate of eBooks vs. physical books as she gives her opinion on price, the dilemma of eating while reading and convenience of carrying them around. To see which one wins check out her YouTube channel for yourself!</p> <h2>3. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/Benjaminoftomes\">Benjamin Of Tomes</a> </h2>       <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/Benjaminoftomes\"                                                                        > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?wmode=opaque&list=UUtTBwUBtW9KtYLTcOSTO7_Q\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>   <p>Benjamin is so sweet and even though he is at times a bit over the top we forgive him for it because his enthusiasm for reading is absolutely infectious. He has the usual book hauls, wrap ups and recommendations but he does them with such charm and liveliness. Some of the best videos are where he takes his audience book shopping with him and his Free Book Friday videos are very entertaining. A very good vlogger to follow!</p> <h2>4. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKX0VKoLARCqSFXoolsObLQ\">Tiny Reads</a> </h2>       <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2ZYhFRePBvk\"                                                                        > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2ZYhFRePBvk?wmode=opaque&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>   <p>We recommend this vlogger because she is so passionate about reading. We love in particular her bookshelf tour, her book shopping in London, and her What’s in My Bag video. Tiny Reads also has giveaways which you can enter and even though she is fairly new to the blog scene her channel is definitely one to watch.</p> <h2>5. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/tessaROXX\">Tessa Netting </a></h2>       <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cnxF1iJbmoM\"                                                                        > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cnxF1iJbmoM?wmode=opaque&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>   <p>This one is popular among group because she mostly talks about Harry Potter. Potter merchandising, books and characters are her passion and she is a self-proclaimed Ravenclaw (because of her love for books!). The funniest video on her channel in our opinion (and we watched this at group ALL the way through) is her 100 things to do when you are not at Hogwarts video. If you are a huge Harry Potter fan (like most of us in group are – the Harry vs Draco debate occurs almost every meet!) then you will discover some cool Potter stuff on this channel!</p>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4fv7j","wordcount":"506","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde/0_141_4256_2555/140.jpg","standfirst":"<p>If you’re looking for someone who shares your passion for reading, offers recommendations and maybe even organises a books giveaway every now and then, then watching YouTube book vloggers is perfect for you. Book group <strong>Millennium RIOT Readers</strong> share their 5 favourites</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/06/top-5-youtube-book-vloggers","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/06/top-5-youtube-book-vloggers","sectionName":"Children's books","elements":[{"id":"12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde/0_141_4256_2555/2000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"© keith morris / Alamy","picdarUrn":"GD*54667538","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde","suppliersReference":"C6YB19","altText":"Teenage girl on laptop","caption":"Teenage girl on laptop","photographer":"keith morris / Alamy","source":"Alamy","credit":"Photograph: keith morris / Alamy/Alamy","mediaId":"12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde","displayCredit":"true","imageType":"Photograph","secureFile":"https://media.guim.co.uk/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde/0_141_4256_2555/2000.jpg","width":"2000","height":"1201"},"mimeType":"image/jpeg"},{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde/0_141_4256_2555/1000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"© keith morris / Alamy","picdarUrn":"GD*54667538","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/12a5e63c5f81616b0cf9b6b9d96496a2c8a2afde","suppliersReference":"C6YB19","altText":"Teenage girl on laptop","ca