ve Berlin to the desolate countryside of Germany. Lonely Bruno longs to explore the forbidden world around him and, in some parallel existence divided by tall wired walls, Bruno meets Shmuel.</p> <p>Their friendship defies expectations. Learning about one another’s oppositional worlds, the pair’s innocence suspends the malevolence of the Holocaust for a short while. Yet, as Bruno finally crosses the divide that segregates them, their friendship results in devastating consequences.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"fdc408f57d257129f16b549af8980b97a664e4b3\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/fdc408f57d257129f16b549af8980b97a664e4b3/39_0_1800_1080/1000.jpg\" alt=\"the boy in the striped pyjamas  film still\" width=\"1000\" height=\"600\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">Bruno meets Shmuel; a still from the 2008 film adaptation of The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas, directed by Mark Herman.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Rex</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <p>The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas acts as a poignant fable, offering a unique perspective on a hideous reality. Here are some unforgettable quotes to mark 10 years of Boyne’s allegorical story:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Despite the chaos that followed, Bruno found that he was still holding Shmuel’s hand in his own and nothing in the world would have persuaded him to let go.”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Their lost voices must continue to be heard.”</p> </blockquote> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2015/dec/10/top-10-unlikely-friendships-in-childrens-books\">Top 10 unlikely friendships in children’s books</a> </p> </aside>  <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>He looked up at the skies, and although they were still very dark he thought the day had probably had enough rain.”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>But still there are moments when a brother and sister can lay down their instruments of torture for a moment and speak as civilized human beings and Bruno decided to make this one of those moments.”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Nothing, thought Bruno, not even the insects, would ever choose to stay at Out-With.”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>And who decided which people wore the striped pyjamas and which people wore the uniforms?”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Father laughed, which upset Bruno even more; there was nothing that made him more angry than when a grown-up laughed at him for not knowing something, especially when he was trying to find out the answer by asking questions.”</p> </blockquote> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">How do I get involved in the Guardian children's books site?</a> </p> </aside>  <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Bruno had read enough books about explorers to know that one could never be sure what one was going to find.”</p> </blockquote> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Just because a man glances up at the sky at night does not make him an astronomer, you know.”</p> </blockquote> <p><strong>Have we missed any of your favourite The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas quotes? You can either email them to <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site\">childrens.books@theguardian.com</a> or share on Twitter </strong><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/GdnChildrensBks\">@GdnChildrensBks</a>!</strong><br /></p>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4fgqb","wordcount":"383","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8/0_1451_2001_1203/140.jpg","standfirst":"<p>To celebrate 10 years of John Boyne’s heartbreaking Holocaust tale The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas, here’s our selection of powerful quotes from the novel</p><p>You can share your favourite The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas quotes with us on Twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GdnChildrensBks\">@GdnChildrensBks</a> or by email childrens.books@theguardian.com</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/05/the-boy-in-the-striped-pyjamas-john-boyne-quotes","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/05/the-boy-in-the-striped-pyjamas-john-boyne-quotes","sectionName":"Children's books","elements":[{"id":"60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8/0_1451_2001_1203/2000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"THIS COPYRIGHTED IMAGE MUST NOT BE USED WITHOUT PERMISSION","picdarUrn":"DB*3559703","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8","suppliersReference":"793517","altText":"Boy in the striped pyjamas","caption":"A scene from the film version of The Boy In Striped Pyjamas, made in 2008.","photographer":"c.Miramax/Everett","source":"Rex Features","credit":"Photograph: c.Miramax/Everett/Rex Features","mediaId":"60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8","displayCredit":"true","imageType":"Photograph","secureFile":"https://media.guim.co.uk/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8/0_1451_2001_1203/2000.jpg","width":"2000","height":"1202"},"mimeType":"image/jpeg"},{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8/0_1451_2001_1203/1000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"THIS COPYRIGHTED IMAGE MUST NOT BE USED WITHOUT PERMISSION","picdarUrn":"DB*3559703","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/60df66600627b1531ad4f27bc410cdc52e7b79c8","suppliersReference":"793517","altText":"Boy in the striped pyjamas","caption":"A scene from the film version of The Boy In Stripe